Text.SourceString: Yes? May I help you?//<portrait=happy>My name’s <NPCName>Luke</>. Pleasure is mine.
Interesting… Moving to a small island from Pokyo is an odd choice.//<portrait=normal>And why now? But I suppose everyone has their own reasons.//Good luck with…things.
I don’t get why Mother keeps complaining about the recycling center. I walked past it yesterday, and it smelled fine.

I don’t mind paying a little extra in tax if it goes directly toward fixing up the buildings around here. But that’s not always the case, and unfortunately I don’t agree with some of this town’s current spending.
The seasonal decorations, for instance… I don’t think we need to spend any more of the budget on that.
I read that the early civilization here used to farm together and share their harvest. It was the law of the land.
It probably worked because it was a much simpler time back then. Nowadays, to run something as simple as a community garden, I think we’d need some sort of permit. Hmm…
I won’t be much use at gardening. I learned a thing or two from Mother, but I have no, umm… What do they call it?
Ah, yes, I have no green thumb… No talent for growing plants.
I read that the early civilization here used to farm together and share their harvest. It was the law of the land.
It probably worked because it was a much simpler time back then. Nowadays, to run something as simple as a community garden, I think we’d need some sort of permit. Hmm…
I absolutely love Mondays. In fact, today is the most important day of the week for me. It’s when I recuperate from the weekend.
*humming what sounds like a sad song*
I used to work on Mondays, but there wasn’t much business.
People are too busy to shop at the beginning of the week, I suppose. So here I am.
The weather is nice today… I should do things, like go to the beach or something. Feels like a waste otherwise.
But I won’t. Well, technically, it’s more like I can’t. I have work that’ll keep me busy for at least the next two or three days.
Shopping day? Tuesdays are when people usually shop and submit their orders.
Have you seen the new item that I’ve got in stock?
You can see my commercial on TV every other day. But I usually only add new stock on the weekend.
Not always, though. Might want to keep that in mind.
Ugh… You have quite a style.
It’s distinctive, to say the least.
I think I’ll change my display today.
How’s your week been so far? You look like you haven’t slept much.
My store is closed tomorrow. I usually do some bookkeeping at home instead.
I don’t like fishing. You just sit around doing nothing for a long time, waiting for a fish to take the bait.//Doesn’t seem productive to me.
All the waiting around… It’s all for a fish. One fish. Yeah, can’t do that.
Aren’t you supposed to be working?
I’m both for and against taking breaks from work.
I think it’s equally important to work hard and to understand our limits.
How are you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Nothing much, thank you for asking.
<NpcName>Taco</> is my dog. He followed <NpcName>Suki</> out of the forest and sort of lives here now.//He sleeps at my house.
<NpcName>Taco</> likes to roam around on his own. He’s a true adventurer.
Oh, good Goddess! What happened to you? Did you get attacked?
Oh, good! I just never really know with you, I guess. Because you always look so, um, casual.
I’m just going to take it slow today.
Are you submitting an order?
You don’t have to, but you should.
Has anyone ever told you that you talk a lot? It’s a bit counterproductive when you’re trying to work.
I can never decide on my favorite grape. I want to say yuscat grape because you can both eat it and turn it into wine.
But does that mean my decision is merely based on convenience? Will I change my mind if, perhaps, I take flavor into account?
I need to think about this.
They just increased the price of ads. Again! Unbelievable.
How am I supposed to make a profit? I can’t increase my price.
The islanders won’t be able to afford my items if I increase my price. I’d risk running out of customers, and then I would go out of business.
I might go to the beach tomorrow. Visit the shack or something.
Hmm… I should wear a hat.
Running errands, are we?
Your boots are dirty, by the way. Perhaps one of these days you can go by the creek and clean them?
Only if you want to. You certainly don’t have to. But judging by the look of your boots, you already know that.
Ugh… I did it again. Sorry if I sounded condescending. I didn’t mean to.
Do you have a favorite grape?
You seem surprised. Why? Did I surprise you?
I can never decide on my favorite grape. I want to say yuscat grape because you can both eat it and turn it to wine.
But does that mean my decision is merely based on convenience? Will I change my mind if, perhaps, I take flavor into account?
I need to think about this.
I have to ship out tons of wine from the vineyard tomorrow at dawn. I got the paperwork done today, and hopefully the boat will arrive on time.
Hmm… I may need to order some extra TVs to sell. They seem to be flying off the shelves.
TVs are expensive to stock, though. I’m not sure what to do. I find that people tend to buy more when I have TVs on display. The problem is, I don’t have actual data to back up my theory.
I just got this cool speaker in this week’s shipment. I’m going to test it out at <NpcName>Pablo</>’s and see if I should keep it or not.
Sorry, I have a “no returns” policy at Socket. My supplier only gives me flexibility in my personal orders. Even then, it’s constrained to TVs and speakers, not kitchen appliances.
I grew my hair out one time, and it was very hot.
Not that it looked hot. I meant “hot” as in body temperature.//It made me sweat a lot.
My weekend plans? Hmm… Good question.
I don’t know yet. I guess it depends on how many orders I receive and process today.
It’s hard to decide on gifts. How do you know someone’s tastes haven’t changed since the last time you gave them something?
My personal go-to for a gift is to buy them a meal from the tavern. If folks don’t like that, it’s nothing personal, right?
I was minding my own business at the library the other day, reading, and somebody tapped me on the shoulder.
I was reading. At the library… Does that not show that I don’t want to be bothered?//A lot of us need to learn to read the room better.
I don’t want to alarm you, but you have to hear about this book. It claimed that a lot of different magical creatures used to live on this island.
I mean, maybe there was a Goddess. But mermaids? Not only mermaids, but a clan of them? It claimed an ancient kingdom of mermaids lived on Coral Island… Huh?
What’s next? A group of frogs ruling the country? I can’t decide if I’m amused or confused.
I’m not one to care about farming or to poke around in other people’s personal lives. But how are things with you and your farm, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I like the sound of that!

Special.SourceString: Its going well. Plant plant plant, harvest harvest harvest. Ka'ching!

Text.SourceString: It was literal trash. This is ridiculous!

Special.SourceString: It is literally none of your business. I refuse to answer, just like you refused to accept my bad gifts.

Text.SourceString: So sorry, <PlayerName>$player</>. That is so sad.

Special.SourceString: Its not good. I am nose-diving into bankruptcy

Text.SourceString: Lamps and blenders? Is that what I’ve become to this island? Everyone just thinks of me as the lamp-and-blender guy.
Not my parents, though. To them, I’m the wine merchant.//I’m the one making sure their winery turns a profit. *sighs*
It’s a jolly day, for sure. And I shall treat it as such. I’m done complaining for the week.
It's lively here on Saturday, isn’t it?
I’m feeling a little antsy. I think I’m just ready for Summer.
This year’s Consumer Electronics Expo was amazing. Too bad I could only stream it…//I wasn’t able to get tickets.

It’s always cool to see new technology. That’s why the Consumer Electronics Expo is the <Italic>one</> event I’m looking forward to in Spring…//<portrait=concerned>Well, that’s not true. I also like the Cherry Blossom Festival.
One of the coolest things I saw at the Consumer Electronics Expo has to be self-driving cars… When they were first introduced.//I thought it was groundbreaking… Hmm…

The smart bathtub was amazing too. You set your preferred temperature, and it does everything for you.//It does the filling up, makes sure the temperature is perfect, and drains automatically when you’re done.

Spring happens to be the beginning of the life cycle of electronics, like it is for many things in life and nature. It’s when new things are introduced to the market.//Exciting time for farmers too, I suppose. With the going back to farming and whatnot.
I know it’s Summer, but I can’t bring myself to wear shorts.//I live on a hill behind a vineyard… If I wore shorts, I’m afraid I’d get eaten alive by mosquitos.
There aren’t any exciting announcements for electronics this Summer. All that was done in the Spring.//Let’s wait and see what the reviews say!
I have to say, I’m enjoying Summer more than I expected…even with the bugs and all.
What is it about Summer that makes me want to pick up my clubs and go golfing?//It’s all those Summer camps my parents sent me to, I suppose. The memories stick.
The town is lively in Summer.//I like it.
<NPCName>Nina</> and I used to go sailing with our fathers every Summer. We stopped because her father…//<portrait=sad>Well, you know.
I don’t think I’ve seen Father sailing since I was a boy. I haven’t gone in a while either.//<portrait=normal>Maybe I should ask him.
People who think tomato soup is best in Fall are clearly wrong.//<portrait=normal>Tomatoes are a Summer crop and thus best consumed during Summer.
What did you do in Summer when you were a kid?
You can sleep in other seasons as well, you know. But I see your point.//I used to go to camps abroad, and sometimes, sleeping in wasn’t part of the package. Ha ha!
Yes, I did too. Sailing was nice. The sea is always one of my favorite places to be.//Tennis camps were fun. You’re gone for a whole season and come back improved by the time school starts.
Yes, I did as well, in between Summer camps.//Unfortunately, some of them, like the tennis camp in San Franciskyo, didn’t let us bring any games.
I wish I could spend more time at Sockets, but it’s harvest season, and the winery is just sucking up most of my time.
Are you as busy as we are in Fall?//<portrait=concerned>It’s honestly such a pain. But it is what it is…
I need to make sure we have enough time to process and ship orders before Winter hits.
We do have a greenhouse where we grow grapes, but the taste never quite matches the grapes we harvest in Fall.//That’s just my personal opinion.
I’ve been knee-deep in reviews of this year’s Consumer Electronics Expo.//Definitely looking forward to the online end-of-year sale. There are things that I’d like to get my hands on.

I go to a small electronics store in Tosaka. It has lots of things I need.//You can check out their speakers from low end to high end. That way, you can compare them for yourself right there and then.//Size doesn’t matter when it comes to electronic stores.
Are you warm in those, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I think the sweater I’m wearing is sufficient for Fall .No need to wear thick coats just yet.

If you need more layers for Winter, White Flamingo usually has great sweaters.//I get mine from there… Though sometimes they have some questionable things…like giant animal onesies.//Fashion, I suppose. I don’t quite understand.
Phew, things have finally slowed down at the winery.//Mother can take care of the greenhouse, and all that’s left is filling orders and doing paperwork. Easy.
Are you coming to Mother’s party? You should. We usually have an amazing spread and fun games all night.
Now that it’s Winter, there are massive electronics sales everywhere!//I might check out the electronics district in Pokyo. Let’s see how the week goes!
I can’t wait for the Consumer Electronics Expo this Spring.//I wonder what <Italic>weird</> stuff they’ll have!
I’m so glad Fall is over and done with. Now I can put more energy into Sockets.
We do grow grapes in the greenhouse in Winter, but we don’t rely too much on them. They’re sort of like a backup supply.
Shouldn’t you start farming or something?
If you need to buy seeds, go to Sam’s General Store. He carries a variety.
Pufferfish Corporation owns that building, you know. We found out last Fall when we tried to lease the building for our tasting room.
They rejected our offer without any explanation. Now we know why.
I don’t know about Pokyo, but deep-fried bananas are a thing around here. <NPCName>Joko</> loves them.
There are plenty of flowers around. You can find tulips and violets around the lake if that’s your thing.
How do you even choose which ones to pick?
Did you do anything fun to celebrate the New Year?
Tomorrow is the Cherry Blossom Festival. I think it's the highlight of the year on Coral Island.
Gah… That was a bold statement, wasn’t it? I even surprised myself.
It’s nearly the end of Spring already. I feel like I haven’t done much.
People tend to buy more outdoor grills this time of year. Maybe they’re getting ready for Summer cookouts.
That wasn’t a wild guess. I looked at the sales numbers. Well, in any case, it’s good for business.
I guess this’ll be the last week we can enjoy the cherry blossoms this year.
Cherry blossoms are so beautiful, yet their lives are so tragically short. Perhaps like life…
That was a song lyric, wasn’t it?//From the Shell Rockers? Gosh, I love that band.
[Luke hums a sad song by the Shell Rockers.]
Wow… The first week of Summer, and the mosquitos are already out in full force.
I always do the same thing on Saturdays.//I suppose you’re right.
Huh… I feel like you’ve asked me that already.//<portrait=normal>In any case, I find star fruit aesthetically pleasing, but a tad too bitter for my taste.
Why do you care so much about star fruit?
We’re cleaning up the beach next Saturday, <PlayerName>$player</>. Come prepared!
We have a duty to take care of Mother Nature. If not us, then who will?
I can’t believe next week is Fall already.
It’s still so hot! It doesn’t seem to cool down one bit. Or is it just me?
<NPCName>Nina</> and I used to hunt ghosts when we were nine or ten years old.//On windy nights, we got to stay up and eat ramen outside her villa.
Her parents were okay with it. Our families are very close… Ah, fun times.
It’s the new season! I’ve got new items in stock.
How do you keep warm in your cabin on Fall nights?
Errr… I have some heater recommendations, if you’d like.
I ordered some heaters for the ranch, and they haven’t arrived. Disaster!
Winter is around the corner. This is unprofessional! I should give them a call.
Look at how much snow has accumulated, and we’re not even a week into Winter.
So what are you going to do for the next three or four weeks, now that you can’t really farm?
The vineyard will rely on the greenhouse. Our production is declining. But it’s on purpose.
I’m always intrigued by the things <NPCName>Ben</> manages to find on his Fall escapades.
Have you checked them out? They’re fascinating, to say the least.//<portrait=normal>One time, I saw a puppet made out of wood with a coconut shell for a head. It was all dressed up. Very odd.
Excited for the New Year?
Yeah, my family has a New Year’s Eve dinner tradition.//So, if nothing else comes up, we’ll probably just spend the day preparing for that.
Mother once told me that after I marry, she wants me to continue the family tradition, and she still expects me to spend New Year’s Eve with her, wherever I end up.
I don’t care much about it, but it seems important to her. So, I’ll make sure to do it. At the end of the day, it’s the least I can do after all the things my parents have done for me.
I hope you’re going to the New Year’s Eve dinner at the vineyard.
I don’t mind the rain.
Well… I actually do, a little.
It depends, I guess. I don’t mind it today.
The rain isn’t that bad. First of all, it’s not too windy, and it’s not pouring rain.//It’s sprinkling and cool, but not so heavy that I have to put my rubber boots on.
I feel a bit gloomy today.
I don’t mind the rain.
Well, you know what, <PlayerName>$player</>? I actually do mind the rain a little.
I don’t mind the rain today.
It isn’t too windy, and it’s not pouring rain. It’s sprinkling and cool, but not raining so hard that I have to put my rubber boots on.
I don’t mind the rain.
Well, you know what, <PlayerName>$player</>? I actually do mind the rain a little.
I don’t mind the rain.
It isn’t too windy, and it’s not pouring rain. It’s sprinkling and cool, but not raining so hard that I have to put my rubber boots on.
I don't like storms.
They scare me a little.
I don't like storms.
They scare me a little.
Excuse me… I’m kind of in a rush.
Excuse me… I’m kind of in a rush.
Do you have any cousins that you’re close with, <PlayerName>$player</>?//For some reason, snowy days always remind me of my cousins and that one eccentric uncle.
Have you got one of those too?
I have two. One from each side of the family. Lucky me.
You have some snow on your clothes.
Do you have any cousins that you’re close with, <PlayerName>$player</>?//For some reason, snowy days always remind me of my cousins and that one eccentric uncle.
Have you got one of those too?
I have two. One from each side of the family. Lucky me.
I found an onyx lying around in my cash register drawer one time. I gave it to <NpcName>Rafael</> and he was thrilled.
Eh… I had no use for it, anyway.
Do you have any cousins that you’re close with, <PlayerName>$player</>?//For some reason, snowy days always remind me of my cousins and that one eccentric uncle.
Have you got one of those too?
I have two. One from each side of the family. Lucky me.
I can feel the snow through my sweater, straight to my bones.
I should have stayed home today.
I make sure to bring lunch from home.
People ask a lot of questions without reading the user manual first.
Why would they think I have better information than the literal user manual?
Oh, hey, submitting an order?
I’m probably just going to eat my lunch in front of my computer and get things done.//No plans…
Just some green salad... Nothing fancy.
With herbed tempeh and lemon dressing.
Oh, darn! I forgot to shut my bedroom door.
<NpcName>Taco</> is going to make a huge mess in there. *sighs*
Looking for my father? Hmm… I honestly don’t know where he might be.
Have you tried the vineyard? He could be in the greenhouse.
We offered to let <NpcName>Ben</> stay at the house, but he refused.
I think he likes to live by himself.
<NpcName>Ben</> is a good friend of mine, but I still tell him that some of his items are overpriced junk.
I disagree. I believe, in this case, that honesty is the best policy.
There is no better way to spend the day than being outside, especially in weather like this.
There’s so much more to running a vineyard than shipping wine. I have to maintain relationships with our buyers, which means inviting them over for dinner every once in a while.
I keep my business relationships separate from personal ones. With good business partners, I can’t risk getting too close and harming the relationship.
Hmm… I think I’ll chill here today. I’m too tired to go to the tavern.
I might go to the tavern later. I’m craving a big plate of pasta!
Hmm… I think I’ll chill here today. I’m too tired to go to the tavern.
Tradition is what links us to our past, and hopefully to our future as well.
Care for a drink, <PlayerName>$player</>?
